{"id":"turquoise-trail","generatedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z","designation":"National Scenic Byway","parkCode":null,"source":{"roadArticle":"New Mexico State Road 14","revisionId":1300234750,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Mexico_State_Road_14"},"attribution":{"license":"CC BY-SA 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","articleUrl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Mexico_State_Road_14","text":"Route, junction, and history details adapted from the Wikipedia article \"New Mexico State Road 14\", by Wikipedia contributors, licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0."},"sources":[{"name":"Wikipedia","src":"wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Mexico_State_Road_14","revisionId":1300234750,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"Federal Highway Administration — National Scenic Byways","src":"fhwa","url":"https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/byways","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)","src":"osm","url":"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"}],"endpoints":{"from":"Tijeras, NM","to":"Santa Fe, NM","via":["San Antonito, NM","No major junctions, NM","Golden, NM"]},"itinerary":[{"seq":1,"place":"Tijeras","state":"NM","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":0,"toNextMi":6,"note":"The drive begins here","control":["Albuquerque","Edgewood"],"lat":35.0941,"lng":-106.1915,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":2,"place":"San Antonito","state":"NM","kind":"town","mileFromStart":6,"toNextMi":null,"note":"Junction toward Sandia Park & Sandia Peak","control":["Sandia Park","Sandia Peak"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":3,"place":"No major junctions","state":"NM","kind":"town","mileFromStart":null,"toNextMi":null,"note":"Junction toward No major junctions","control":["No major junctions"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":4,"place":"Golden","state":"NM","kind":"town","mileFromStart":15.7,"toNextMi":36.6,"note":"Junction toward Edgewood","control":["Edgewood"],"lat":35.22544,"lng":-106.15744,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":5,"place":"Santa Fe","state":"NM","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":52.3,"toNextMi":null,"note":"The drive ends here","control":["NM 466 east (Saint Michaels Drive)"],"lat":35.22544,"lng":-106.15744,"src":"wikipedia"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["State Road 10 (NM 10) had been established before 1927 between Albuquerque and Santa Fe. By 1927, part of NM 10 was replaced by US 470 from Tijeras to Albuquerque, but the northern terminus remained at US 85 in Santa Fe. By 1930, the end of NM 10 was at US 66. In 1935, NM 10 was extended south to NM 15 near Tajique. NM 15 was later absorbed into a further southern extension of NM 10 to US 54 in Carrizozo. By 1949, this highway was mostly paved.","Originally, the NM 14 designation was serviced by a road between the Arizona–New Mexico state line and US 80 in Road Forks. NM 14 along with SR 86 in Arizona provided a shortcut to US 80 between Benson, Arizona and Road Forks, due to US 80 taking a loop to Douglas, Arizona. The original NM 14 was replaced by Interstate 10 in 1960.","In 1970, the NM 14 designation was recycled and used to re-number NM 10, to avoid numbering confusion with I-10. During the 1988 re-numbering, NM 14 was extended along former US 85 through Santa Fe to US 84 and US 285, while the concurrency with NM 333 was eliminated. The sections of NM 14 south of NM 333 were renumbered NM 337 and NM 55 respectively."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"Tijeras","d":"The drive begins here","q":"Tijeras","lat":35.095,"lng":-106.37,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Santa Fe","d":"The drive ends here","q":"Santa Fe","lat":35.66722222,"lng":-105.96444444,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"\"Posted Route–Legal Description\" (PDF). New Mexico Department of Transportation. March 16, 2010. p. 5. Retrieved December 20, 2013.","url":"http://dot.state.nm.us/content/dam/nmdot/Data_Management/POSTED%20ROUTE-NM_Routes.pdf"},{"n